* A METHOD can have "normal" parameters along with variable-length parameter.
However, the variable-length parameter must be the LAST parameter declared by the
METHOD
    - E.g int doIt(int a, int b, double c, int .. vals) { }
        * The first 3 arguments used in a call to doIt() are matched to the first
          three parameters. Then the remaining arguments are assumed to belong to vals

    !!INCORRECT
    int doIt(int a, int b, double c, int ... vals, boolean stopFlag) { }
There MUST BE ONLY ONE VARARGS parameter
    !!INCORRECT
    int doIt(int a, int b, double c, int ... vals, double ... morevals) { }